# Quality Autopilot - Windsurf Rules

1. Read .instructions.md FIRST - This is the mandatory system instruction file for all AI coding agents.
2. Read AGENTS.md SECOND - This is the single source of truth for all coding work (architecture, patterns, conventions).
3. Read CHECKLIST.md THIRD - Master implementation checklist with gated phases.
4. Read CLAUDE.md - Quick reference for architecture overview and key files.
5. Use ONLY Agno framework (agno.agent.Agent, agno.team.Team, agno.workflow.Workflow, agno.os.AgentOS).
6. DO NOT introduce LangChain, CrewAI, AutoGen, LlamaIndex, or any other agent framework.
7. Use PostgreSQL + PgVector for all agent databases (DO NOT use SQLite).
8. Follow the exact parameter ordering defined in AGENTS.md Section IV.2 for Agent constructors.
9. Use TeamMode.coordinate for all teams (no other modes unless explicitly approved).
10. Every agent/team/workflow gets its own directory with standard files (agent.py, instructions.py, __init__.py).
11. All hand-offs between agents use Pydantic contracts defined in contracts/.
12. Follow the gated roadmap - never work on Phase N+1 until Phase N's gate is cleared.
13. Use absolute imports only, rooted at the project package.
14. Section headers must use 75-char # --- block separators.
15. Line length max 120 characters (ruff).
16. All code must pass mypy with check_untyped_defs = true.
17. No hardcoded sleep(), waitForTimeout(), CSS selectors, or secrets.
18. Use data-testid, role, or text strategies for Playwright locators.
19. Use FileTools to write files to disk (do not just show in chat).
20. Follow "Look-Before-You-Leap" pattern for the Engineer agent.
21. **Automatic GitHub Push**: After completing a task/phase and receiving Judge approval (≥90% confidence), Cascade must:
    - Create a feature branch (e.g., `feat/discovery-agent`)
    - Commit changes with conventional commit format: `type: description` (e.g., `feat: add Discovery Agent`)
    - Push to GitHub without requiring user consent
    - Branch to main merge happens via PR process (not automatic)
